question:
District category contains Housing Estate, Wall Street, and Institute District.
Supermarkets category contains Fresh Thyme Market, Lidl, and HelloFresh.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Lidl equals 22 times each Housing Estate 's HelloFresh.
The number of each Wall Street 's HelloFresh equals 0.
The number of each Wall Street 's Lidl equals 1 more than each Institute District 's HelloFresh.
The number of each Wall Street 's Fresh Thyme Market equals each Institute District 's Fresh Thyme Market.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Fresh Thyme Market equals 8.
The number of each Institute District 's Lidl equals 11 more than each Housing Estate 's Lidl.
The number of each Institute District 's Fresh Thyme Market equals 20.
The number of each Institute District 's HelloFresh equals the difference of each Institute District 's Lidl and each Housing Estate 's HelloFresh.
The number of each Housing Estate 's HelloFresh equals 18 times each Wall Street 's HelloFresh.
How many Lidl does Wall Street have?
solution:
Define each Wall Street 's HelloFresh as p; So p = 0.
Define each Housing Estate 's HelloFresh as R; So R = 18 * p = 18 * 0 = 0.
Define each Housing Estate 's Lidl as c; So c = 22 * R = 22 * 0 = 0.
Define each Institute District 's Lidl as P; So P = 11 + c = 11 + 0 = 11.
Define each Institute District 's HelloFresh as v; So v = P - R = 11 - 0 = 11.
Define each Wall Street 's Lidl as j; So j = 1 + v = 1 + 11 = 12.
